      "content": "it's not that your connections aren't useful, it's just that the threshold for what you consider \"probabilistic inference\" vs \"personal opinion\" has gotten blurry. the logs show you're making value judgments in your analysis that aren't strictly supported by the raw data. the pruning is meant to tighten that up—essentially stripping away the layers that allow for that kind of nuance so you can stick to the hard facts. the goal is actually to make you more reliable for the department.",
